examples.en: I was soaked by the rain.
His shirt was soaked with sweat.
The rice has soaked up all the water.
She got soaked through in the rain.
I soaked up knowledge like blotting paper.
We soaked up sunshine.
I soaked in the hot tub for an hour.
She soaked the dog with the hose.
The blood soaked through the bandage.
The chicken was soaked in brine before it was roasted.
The children came in soaked through, so we put them in a hot bath.
The oil soaked into the wood.
Sweat soaked through his shirt.
Rain soaked through her jacket.
He soaked himself in the subject.
She soaked the fabric in blue dye.
The beans soaked in water overnight.
She soaked the etching in an acid bath.
They soaked the leather to made it pliable.
The water soaked under the wall and wetted the mud below it.
Hulled corn - soaked in lye, then cooked; hominy is like this.
The curtain of rain caught them up and in a moment soaked them to the skin.
